research_municipality_step.notes: Whitesboro, TX operates under a General Law Type A government, which is a form of mayor-council government. The city council consists of the Mayor and five Aldermen who are elected at-large. Jeff Butts was elected Mayor in May 2025. Carla Woolsey serves as Mayor Pro Tem and an Alderman. The other Aldermen are Su Welch, Mike Pack, Ronnie Fielder, and John Moore.
